on.\n\nThe configuration settings are managed through `AsyncMessageReceiveActionSettings`, which includes the form class package name as a required property and an optional received sequence number generator object.\n\nI'm checking the cross-references and hyperlink targets to preserve them correctly, then compiling the search hints with relevant classes, methods, and keywords for both sections. I'm now describing the `AsyncMessageReceiveAction` class, which is a typical business action handler in the messaging receive architectural pattern that stores data records from incoming messages into a specified table for later batch processing. The received message storage table has two key components: a received message sequence number that serves as the primary key for uniquely identifying each message, generated via `generateReceivedSequence()`, and business message fields that vary depending on the message type.\n\nI should note an important constraint: this class assumes one message maps to one database record, so if the business logic requires storing a single message across multiple records or tables, a custom handler class extending this one would need to be created instead.\n\nNow I'm outlining the handler processing flow, starting with the inbound path where the entire business data section of the request message gets parsed using the default formatter to extract the data record. 例外処理として、フォームクラスがクラスパス上に見つからない場合や、コンストラクタが存在しない、あるいはコンストラクタ実行時にエラーが発生した場合は実行時例外を送出する。設定項目は `AsyncMessageReceiveActionSettings` に集約されており、フォームクラスのパッケージ名やシーケンスジェネレータなどのプロパティで構成されている。\n\nGenerating configuration table...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21822,"cache_read_input_tokens":29889,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21822,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4ff4c23b-c0f8-45b8-acd4-eb00a4f08608","uuid":"07955a65-f9